rresponding laminar unstretched flame\nwhen moving from the fresh to the burnt gas regions. Finally we discuss the\neffects of the turbulence on the thermo-diffusive instability showing that the\nturbulent fluctuations, increasing the flame front corrugations, are\nessentially responsible of the local flame quenching.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 16 Feb 2017 20:46:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-20"}
